# 4. Ingestion Phase Evaluation

The **Ingestion Phase** prepares documents before retrieval.

Several design choices influence retrieval quality.

---

## A. Chunking Experiments

Chunking is one of the most important parameters in RAG.

Different chunk sizes produce different retrieval quality.

Example

Experiment 1

```
Chunk Size = 300

Overlap = 50
```

Experiment 2

```
Chunk Size = 600

Overlap = 100
```

Evaluation helps determine which chunking strategy retrieves more relevant information.

---

## B. Embedding Model Experiments

Different embedding models produce different vector representations.

Examples

- OpenAI Embeddings
- BGE
- E5
- Instructor
- Ollama Embeddings

We compare them using evaluation metrics to identify the model that captures semantic meaning most effectively.

---

## C. Vector Database Experiments

The vector database also influences retrieval performance.

Examples

- ChromaDB
- FAISS
- Pinecone
- Qdrant
- Milvus

Different databases use different indexing techniques and retrieval algorithms.

Evaluation helps determine which database performs best for the application.

